div.h2: GET /stats/:code Parallel Query Plan & Data Flow
div.p: All 4 queries are read-only SELECT; no locks held; safe to run concurrently via errgroup.
SQL A Total Clicks sql SELECT COUNT(*) FROM clicks WHERE short_code = $1
Index: idx_clicks_short_code_time (short_code, clicked_at DESC) Leading column = short_code Index Scan
SQL B Clicks Last 24 h sql SELECT COUNT(*) FROM clicks WHERE short_code = $1 AND clicked_at >= $2
Index: Composite (short_code, clicked_at) Index Range Scan; no heap fetch needed.
SQL C Clicks Last 7 d sql SELECT COUNT(*) FROM clicks WHERE short_code = $1 AND clicked_at >= $2
Index: Same idx_clicks_short_code_time Wider time range larger index range scan.
SQL D Top 5 Referers sql SELECT referer, COUNT(*) AS cnt FROM clicks WHERE short_code = $1 AND referer IS NOT NULL GROUP BY referer ORDER BY cnt DESC LIMIT 5
Index: Partial (short_code, referer) WHERE referer IS NOT NULL.

tr.td: (short_code, referer) WHERE referer IS NOT NULL

ul.li: SELECT-only; no locks acquired; no snapshot conflicts.
pgxpool uses independent connections per query.
